article.headline: Austin Peay 78, Jacksonville St. 63
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- Drake Reed scored a game-high 23 points on 10-of-13 shooting to lead Austin Peay to a 78-63 victory over Jacksonville State Thursday night. The Governors (7-6, 4-1 Ohio Valley Conference) shot 52 percent from the floor in the first and jumped to a 40-29 lead at the half. Wes Channels chipped in a career-best 17 points for Austin Peay while Todd Babington and Fernandez Lockett rounded out the double-digit scoring with 14 and 11 points, respectively. Will Ginn's career-high 20 points for the Gamecocks (3-11, 1-4) was matched by Dorien Brown, but it wasn't enough to overcome Austin Peay's hot first half. Ginn scored 14 of his 20 points in the first half, thanks to a 4-for-6 showing from behind the arc. Both teams shot 47 percent from the floor overall.
